    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-10-08T15:33:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-10-08T15:33:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">771.00/10–852: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d306fn1">This telegram was drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_EHJ1">Elting</persName> (<gloss target="#t_UNP1"
                        >UNP</gloss>) and <persName corresp="#p_MRH1">McBride</persName> (<gloss
                            target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>) and was cleared with <gloss target="#t_AF1"
                            >AF</gloss>. It was repeated to <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>,
                        Rabat, and Tangier.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-10-08T15:33:00-05:00"
                            >October 8, 1952—3:33 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2017. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> has decided handle Moroccan item in
                        <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> in same manner as Tunisian question. For
                    time being we will follow same line with other UN Dels and press as we are
                    presently following re Tunisia: namely, in reply to inquiries from other dels
                        <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> will inform them in confidence of our
                    position; we will reply to press inquiries that we are consulting with other
                    dels on this and other agenda items.<note n="2" xml:id="d306fn2">For details,
                        see documentation on Tunisia, <ref target="#pg_665">pp. 665</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Pls inform <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> of foregoing decision which
                    we gather from <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Hoppenot</persName>’s statement will
                    not be surprising to Fr. <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> will commence answering inquiries on Oct
                    10 along above lines.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
